@startuml
!pragma teoz true
!pragma sequenceMessageSpan true
title Mod Publishing & Admission Pipeline (Ownership Mapping + Dual Gate + Transparency)
hide footbox
autonumber "<color:#8fb6ff><b>[000]</b></color> "
skinparam maxMessageSize 44
skinparam ParticipantPadding 24
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

' =========================
' DARK MODE REVIEW THEME
' =========================

skinparam backgroundColor #121417
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName JetBrains Mono
skinparam defaultFontColor #f3f5f7

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #79b8ff
  ArrowFontColor #f3f5f7

  LifeLineBorderColor #6d7986
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #1f262d

  ParticipantBorderColor #738396
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #25303a
  ParticipantFontColor #ffffff

  ActorBorderColor #98a7b8
  ActorBackgroundColor #2b3742
  ActorFontColor #ffffff

  GroupBorderColor #5f6a75
  GroupBackgroundColor #1a2128
  GroupFontColor #ffffff

  DividerBorderColor #5f6a75
  DividerBackgroundColor #1f262d
  DividerFontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #2a3138
  BorderColor #8b98a6
  FontColor #f3f5f7
}

box "Developer-Controlled Domain" #233447
actor "Namespace Owner\n(GitHub + Steam identity)" as Owner
actor "Mod Developer" as Dev
entity "Source Repo\n(GitHub)" as Repo
control "CI Pipeline\n(Canonical Publisher)" as CI
end box

box "Distribution + Registry Domain" #31283b
actor "Submission Requester\n(anyone)" as Submitter
actor "Registry Moderator" as Moderator
boundary "Steam Workshop" as Steam
control "Registry Verification Gate" as RegGate
database "Namespace Ownership Mapping Index\n(active + alias history)" as OwnershipMapIndex
database "Version Ownership Mapping Snapshots\n(immutable per version)" as VersionOwnershipSnapshots
database "Registry Version Index\n(immutable record + mutable status)" as Registry
database "Version Integrity Tuple Store\n(immutable per version)" as VersionTupleStore
database "Artifact Archive\n(content-addressed cache)" as BinArchive
database "Source + Asset Archive\n(Git snapshot archive)" as SrcArchive
database "Transparency Log\n(append-only hash-chained events)" as TLog
end box

box "Client Runtime Domain" #22362b
control "Launcher" as Launcher
control "Engine Host" as Engine
end box

== Release Authoring ==

Dev -> Repo: Push tag (vX.Y.Z)
Repo -> CI: Trigger release build
activate CI

group CI canonical publication gate
CI -> CI: Build package
CI -> CI: Compute hashes
CI -> CI: Emit CI provenance manifest
end

CI -> Steam: Upload package bytes
CI --> Submitter: Provide CI provenance manifest\n(refs + hashes + build metadata)
deactivate CI

== Registry Admission ==

Owner -> RegGate: Register namespace ownership mapping\n(GitHub + Steam)
Submitter -> RegGate: Submit release request\n(manifest + logged-in identities)
RegGate -> RegGate: Verify CI provenance
RegGate -> RegGate: Verify logged-in GitHub + Steam identities
RegGate -> OwnershipMapIndex: Verify namespace ownership mapping\n(active alias match)
RegGate -> VersionOwnershipSnapshots: Persist version ownership mapping snapshot
RegGate -> RegGate: Validate exact dependency DAG
RegGate -> Steam: Fetch artifact bytes by ref
Steam --> RegGate: Artifact bytes
RegGate -> Repo: Fetch source snapshot by release ref
Repo --> RegGate: Source + asset snapshot
RegGate -> RegGate: Verify artifact/source hashes
RegGate -> BinArchive: Persist verified artifact bytes
RegGate -> SrcArchive: Persist verified source snapshot
RegGate -> VersionTupleStore: Persist immutable version tuple\n(artifact_digest + source_digest + ownership_map_snapshot_id + ci_provenance_id)
RegGate -> Registry: Append immutable version record\n+ initialize status=pending_review
RegGate -> TLog: Append admission event

group Post-admission review pipeline
RegGate -> RegGate: Run automated review checks
alt Automated checks pass
  RegGate -> Registry: Set status=active
  RegGate -> TLog: Append active status event
else Automated checks flag issues
  RegGate -> Registry: Set status=review_required
  RegGate -> Moderator: Open manual review case
  Moderator -> Registry: Set active/deprecated/banned
  Moderator -> TLog: Append moderation event
end
end

== Compromise Response ==

Moderator -> Registry: Mark identity mapping compromised
Registry -> Registry: Block future releases by compromised mapping
Registry -> Registry: Quarantine historical versions by compromised mapping
Moderator -> TLog: Append compromise event

== Client Consumption ==

Launcher -> Registry: Fetch public metadata + status
Registry --> Launcher: Public metadata snapshot\n(non-pending only)
Launcher -> VersionTupleStore: Fetch immutable version tuple
VersionTupleStore --> Launcher: version tuple
Launcher -> BinArchive: Fetch artifact bytes by digest
BinArchive --> Launcher: Artifact bytes
Launcher -> SrcArchive: Fetch source snapshot by digest
SrcArchive --> Launcher: Source snapshot (optional audit)
Launcher -> VersionOwnershipSnapshots: Fetch version ownership mapping snapshot
VersionOwnershipSnapshots --> Launcher: Version ownership mapping snapshot

group Local verification gate
Launcher -> Launcher: Verify content hashes
Launcher -> Launcher: Verify tuple consistency\n(registry + archives + mapping snapshot)
Launcher -> Launcher: Validate dependency DAG
Launcher -> Launcher: Validate namespace ownership mapping snapshot
end

alt status=banned or quarantined
  Launcher --> Launcher: Hard reject
else status=pending_review or review_required
  Launcher --> Launcher: Reject (not public)
else status=deprecated
  Launcher -> Launcher: Warn user\n(and continue)
  Launcher -> Engine: Start with validated set
  activate Engine
  Engine -> Engine: Load core_mod
  Engine -> Engine: Load mods (topological order)
  deactivate Engine
else status=active
  Launcher -> Engine: Start with validated set
  activate Engine
  Engine -> Engine: Load core_mod
  Engine -> Engine: Load mods (topological order)
  deactivate Engine
end

note across
Admission model:
- Namespace ownership mapping is enforced via GitHub + Steam identity matching
- CI publishes canonical provenance manifest
- Registry gate independently verifies and admits
- Registry stores immutable version records + mutable status
- Ownership transfers are represented as alias-history updates
- Immutable version tuple is required for admission and consumption
- Launcher validates against per-version immutable ownership mapping snapshots
- Transparency log records admission/status/compromise events
end note

@enduml
